Ext.data.JsonP['Re-enabling_Test_After_Service_Upgrade']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Re-enabling Test After Service Upgrade</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-43298709\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Re-enabling Test After Service Upgrade</h1>\n    <p>    <span style=\"color: #333333;\">\n     </span>\n    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-warning aui-message problem shadowed information-macro\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Enterprise Subscription Required!</div>\n            <p>This AMPLIFY(<sup class=\" \">TM</sup>) Appcelerator Services feature requires an Enterprise Subscription.    </p>\n    </div>\n        <p>    <span style=\"color: #333333;\">\nWhenever there is an update to the     </span>\n <a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Re-enabling_Test_After_Service_Upgrade\">Appcelerator Test</a>     <span style=\"color: #333333;\">\n service, you must re-enable Test on any Titanium, Android or iOS applications that you had previously enabled, as explained below.    </span>\n    </p>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-43298709_Re-enablingTestAfterServiceUpgrade-Re-enablingTestforTitaniumApplications\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Re-enabling Test for Titanium Applications</span></h2>\n    <p>Titanium developers use Studio to update the plug-in, then re-enable Test in each project&apos;s tiapp.xml file.    </p>\n    <p><strong class=\" \">To install the latest Test module and re-enable Test in a Titanium application</strong>     <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\n:    </span>\n    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>In Studio select <strong class=\" \">Help &gt; Check for Appcelerator Updates</strong>.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click <strong class=\" \">Install</strong> in the Appcelerator Updates dialog that appears.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Once the update is complete, do the following for each Studio project you had previously Test-enabled:    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Open the project&apos;s tiapp.xml file.    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Click <strong class=\" \">Enable Services</strong> in the Appcelerator Services section to re-enable Test. Once enabled, a green check mark appears next to Test.    </p>\n</li></ol></li></ol>    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-43298709_Re-enablingTestAfterServiceUpgrade-Re-enablingTestforiOSandAndroidApplications\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Re-enabling Test for iOS and Android Applications</span></h2>\n    <p>Objective-C, Swift and Java developers need to download the latest <a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Appcelerator_Test_CLI_Reference\">Appcelerator-Test CLI</a> and run it against their projects.    </p>\n    <p><strong class=\" \">To install the latest Appcelerator-Test CLI and re-enable Test in an Android or iOS application</strong>     <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\n:    </span>\n    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>    <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\nLogin to <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"https://platform.appcelerator.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Appcelerator Dashboard</a> and select your application from the App menu.    </span>\n    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>    <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\nOn the application&apos;s <strong class=\" \">Overview</strong> screen, click the <strong class=\" \">Services</strong> tab.    </span>\n    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>    <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\nClick <strong class=\" \">Add Platform Services to your app</strong> on the Services tab.    </span>\n    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>    <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\nClick the <strong class=\" \">Test</strong> tab.    </span>\n    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>    <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\nFollow the instructions shown there to download and run the new CLI tool.     </span>\n     <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\nAlso see the     </span>\n <a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Appcelerator_Test_CLI_Reference\">Appcelerator Test CLI Reference</a>     <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\n for details on using the utility.    </span>\n    </p>\n</li></ol>    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=43298709\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Re-enabling Test After Service Upgrade"});